For running on mips embedded systems (eg. Buffalo routers) 
see extra/mips/toolchain.mak and extra/mips/configure.sh.

Build-time size optimisations yield the following approximate 
savings for the main executable:

* --disable-exec 190k
* --enable-small-exceptions 170k
* --enable-small-config 170k
* --disable-pop 120k
* --disable-auth 100k
* --disable-debug 70k
* --enable-small-fragments 70k
* --disable-admin 60k
* --disable-identity 40k
* --disable-dns 20k

